Is there a way to prevent a blinded split data attack? I don't know what else to call it but consider this:

As a malicious participant, I can create a blinded aggregate array in an ACDC that conforms to a schema such as
```    "A": {
      "oneOf": [
        {
          "description": "Attribute aggregate digest",
          "type": "string"
        },
        {
          "$id": "",
          "description": "Attribute aggregate array",
          "type": "array",
          "minItems": 1,
          "maxItems": 3,
          "items": {
            "anyOf": [
              {
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["d", "u", "i"],
                "properties": {
                  "d": {
                    "description": "SAID of disclosable data",
                    "type": "string"
                  },
                  "u": {
                    "description": "Salty nonce",
                    "type": "string"
                  },
                  "i": {
                    "description": "Issuee AID",
                    "type": "string"    
                  }
